articles.title: Common Painkillers Like Ibuprofen Could Be Fueling a Global Health Threat - SciTechDaily
articles.description: Common painkillers like ibuprofen and acetaminophen may fuel antibiotic resistance, raising urgent questions about drug interactions in aged care and beyond. Ibuprofen and acetaminophen (paracetamol) are among the most widely used pain and fever remedies, but…
articles.content: New research from the University of South Australia suggests that common painkillers like ibuprofen and paracetamol may unintentionally accelerate antibiotic resistance, a major global health concern… [+5326 chars]
